An op amp is an &quot;operational amplifier&quot; which is essentially treated as a
little box that amplifies linearly whatever is put into it. By using
different resistors in a circuit you can adjust the gain of the op amp
circuit.

I&#39;m not sure exactly how Frank is using one for the tuning. It&#39;s not very
common to use an op amp as a noise source but I think it&#39;s been done. There
are better noise sources out there.

Zack


